1
00:00:09,680 --> 00:00:11,440
(CHILDREN LAUGHING)

2
00:00:14,400 --> 00:00:15,400
Hello.

3
00:00:16,680 --> 00:00:17,800
Hello.

4
00:00:18,280 --> 00:00:19,920
Why are you sitting on the swing?

5
00:00:20,560 --> 00:00:23,080
-Why shouldn't I?
-Because you're old.

6
00:00:24,160 --> 00:00:27,680
Yeah, that's true. That, that...
That is very true.

7
00:00:31,320 --> 00:00:33,680
My mum says
I shouldn't talk to strange men.

8
00:00:33,760 --> 00:00:35,080
Ah, your mum's right.

9
00:00:35,680 --> 00:00:38,000
-Are you strange?
-(LAUGHS)

10
00:00:39,120 --> 00:00:41,600
Oh, dear. I'm way past strange.

11
00:00:41,680 --> 00:00:44,600
-I think I'm probably incredible.
-(BOTH LAUGHING)

12
00:00:47,200 --> 00:00:48,400
Are you lonely?

13
00:00:49,400 --> 00:00:52,120
-And why would I be lonely?
-Because you're sad.

14
00:00:52,960 --> 00:00:54,960
-Have you lost something?
-No.

15
00:00:55,400 --> 00:00:58,520
When I lose something,
I go to a quiet place

16
00:00:58,600 --> 00:01:01,640
and I close my eyes
and then I can remember where I put it.

17
00:01:03,280 --> 00:01:05,760
-Good plan.
-I'm always losing things.

18
00:01:05,840 --> 00:01:09,760
I lost my best pencil,
my schoolbag, my gran

19
00:01:09,840 --> 00:01:12,080
-and my mojo.
-Your mojo?

20
00:01:12,160 --> 00:01:14,240
-I got it back, though.
-Hey, that's good.

21
00:01:18,280 --> 00:01:20,720
-What did you lose?
-My friend.

22
00:01:21,640 --> 00:01:24,920
I met her twice before
and I lost her both times

23
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:26,840
and now I don't think
I'll ever find her again.

24
00:01:26,920 --> 00:01:29,840
-Have you been looking?
-Yeah, everywhere.

25
00:01:30,080 --> 00:01:32,160
-That's sad.
-It is a bit.

26
00:01:32,480 --> 00:01:34,440
-Hey. Is that your mum?
-Yeah.

27
00:01:34,520 --> 00:01:35,920
I'd better go and see
if she's all right.

28
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:37,360
Yeah. I think you better had.

29
00:01:37,840 --> 00:01:39,000
How are you going to find her?

30
00:01:40,520 --> 00:01:43,560
Well, the first two times I met her
I just sort of bumped into her,

31
00:01:43,640 --> 00:01:46,680
so I thought maybe if I just

32
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:49,320
wandered about a bit,
I might bump into her again.

33
00:01:49,880 --> 00:01:53,600
You know, like...destiny, sort of.

34
00:01:53,680 --> 00:01:55,560
-That's rubbish.
-(CHUCKLES)

35
00:01:56,200 --> 00:01:57,640
I think it probably is.

36
00:01:58,080 --> 00:02:01,640
Hey, maybe I could find a quiet room
and have a good think about it instead.

37
00:02:01,720 --> 00:02:03,240
-That would be better.
-Yeah.

38
00:02:03,320 --> 00:02:04,800
-Goodbye.
-Goodbye.

39
00:02:08,840 --> 00:02:10,320
Mister!

40
00:02:10,400 --> 00:02:11,920
I hope you find her again.

41
00:02:12,320 --> 00:02:13,560
So do 1.

42
00:02:15,840 --> 00:02:18,000
-Who was that?
-I was talking to a sad man.

43
00:02:18,080 --> 00:02:22,040
Clara Oswald, what have I told you
about talking to strange men?

